1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,510
(Episode 54)

2
00:00:11,850 --> 00:00:13,390
Seriously.

3
00:00:14,650 --> 00:00:17,690
Ma Seo Rin, you were supposed
to stick with me.

4
00:00:49,890 --> 00:00:50,890
Oh my gosh!

5
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:52,920
Mom!

6
00:00:54,530 --> 00:00:56,830
What is wrong with you, Seo Rin?

7
00:00:57,130 --> 00:00:59,600
Why did you put me through this?

8
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:02,470
What happened to you? You're a mess.

9
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,010
Mom, did you walk all the way here?

10
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:09,310
My legs...

11
00:01:09,310 --> 00:01:10,810
My legs are killing me.

12
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:13,650
What on earth happened?

13
00:01:15,210 --> 00:01:18,750
I went back to the bench,
and you weren't there,

14
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,620
so I just assumed you went to the meeting
and took a cab here.

15
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:24,690
Our car was gone. It must've been towed
for being illegally parked.

16
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:27,660
My phone and my purse were in that car!

17
00:01:27,730 --> 00:01:29,790
Oh my gosh. Really?

18
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:33,700
I just assumed you'd call Manager Lee
and handle everything.

19
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,770
For someone as capable as you,
that's a piece of cake.

20
00:01:37,140 --> 00:01:39,370
You're good at everything, Mom.

21
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,040
Father.

22
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,640
How did the meeting go without me...

23
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:48,880
As the CEO of the hotel,
how can you be so unprofessional?

24
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:51,920
Don't even try to make excuses
for missing the meeting.

25
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:54,320
- It's pathetic.
- Father,

26
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,750
I didn't skip it. I was held up.

27
00:01:57,390 --> 00:01:59,520
You heard what happened from Seo Rin.

28
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,730
Will you tell the board of directors
the same thing?

29
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:06,400
Handling a crisis like that
is also a measure of your competence.

30
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,200
You could've just gone
to the police for help.

31
00:02:09,670 --> 00:02:13,740
As if Chae Hwa Young would ever
swallow her pride and lose face like that.

32
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:14,810
Shut up!

33
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:17,440
Are you trying to add fuel
to the fire or what?

34
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:19,240
Mom, you're a complete mess.

35
00:02:19,940 --> 00:02:22,180
I'll run you a bath. Go get cleaned up.

36
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,280
Yes.

37
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:27,490
It seems Seo Rin is the only one
who cares about CEO Chae.

38
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,290
Chae Hwa Young.

39
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:39,860
Compared to what you did
to my mom, dad, and Seo Rin,

40
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:42,370
this pain is nothing.

41
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:45,670
You have a long way to go
before you feel real pain.

42
00:02:46,370 --> 00:02:47,570
This is just the beginning.

43
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:51,910
Please excuse me then.

44
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,560
Here.

45
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:16,070
I found the car
and brought it back for you.

46
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,640
Good.

47
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,110
Chairman.

48
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:23,910
We caught the driver who hit Director Ma.

49
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:27,010
You caught the bastard who hit Seo Rin?

50
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:28,080
Yes, Chairman.

51
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:32,820
We wouldn't have caught him this quickly
without CEO Chae's special directive.

52
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,850
Good. I'm relieved.

53
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:38,090
So, who is the guy
who did this to our Seo Rin?

54
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:40,020
Apparently, he's a former truck driver.

55
00:03:40,330 --> 00:03:43,830
His family is struggling financially,
and he was fired from his job that day.

56
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,830
It seems he wasn't in his right mind.

57
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:47,100
The investigation is ongoing.

58
00:03:47,570 --> 00:03:50,200
Tell him a settlement is
out of the question.

59
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:52,740
A guy like that deserves to rot in jail.

60
00:03:53,570 --> 00:03:54,670
Wouldn't you agree, Father?

61
00:03:54,770 --> 00:03:58,810
Yes. I'm just glad Seo Rin is
recovering well.

62
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:02,050
What? They caught him?

63
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:04,320
How can they tell such a barefaced lie?

64
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:08,290
Chae Hwa Young. You're the one
who tried to have me killed.

65
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,860
You left Seo Rin fighting for her life,

66
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:13,060
and now she's going to
get away with it like this?

67
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,300
It's just that one of the directors
at my company...

68
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,400
got into a car accident yesterday, too.

69
00:04:22,970 --> 00:04:25,770
I was just wondering if it might have been
the same accident.

70
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:30,380
I'm Ma Seo Rin.
I'm the Director of Food and Beverage.

71
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:36,150
Two people with similar faces got
into a car accident at the same time?

72
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,820
Could this really be a coincidence?

73
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,520
If I meet Ma Seo Rin,

74
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:44,890
I feel like I might be able to
solve this puzzle.

75
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:51,760
I've taken care of
all the insurance stuff now, honey.

76
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:53,730
You did?

77
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:56,270
Thinking back,

78
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,870
I'm glad we signed the settlement
and wrapped things up quickly.

79
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:02,110
It's all really over now.

80
00:05:02,670 --> 00:05:04,810
Honey, you've been through so much.

81
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:07,080
Not at all.

82
00:05:07,650 --> 00:05:09,950
You're the one who's been
through the most.

83
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:11,720
You sure picked a good wife, didn't you?

84
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,950
Absolutely.

85
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:17,660
You're absolutely second to none.

86
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:22,590
I've always felt
you were way too good for me.

87
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:26,630
I love hearing that.

88
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:29,900
You have such a way with words.

89
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:34,070
All the men in Korea could learn
a thing or two from you.

90
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:41,050
When I take on cases,
I meet all kinds of characters.

91
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:44,650
But I'll never understand
why most of the husbands are so awful.

92
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:49,450
It's incredible how they can lie
with a straight face.

93
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,090
It's just dumbfounding.

94
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:56,130
Seriously. They have affairs
and still act so high and mighty.

95
00:05:56,630 --> 00:05:57,930
Unbelievable.

96
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,740
How am I still hungry? We just ate.

97
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:09,610
Me too. Should we
make some instant noodles?

98
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:11,610
Put an egg in mine.

99
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,180
I hate eggs in instant noodles.
It makes the broth all murky.

100
00:06:14,450 --> 00:06:16,380
I'll just make it plain.

101
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:29,760
I have to hurry and find the evidence
Seo Rin hid.

102
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,430
That's the only way
I can finally take down Chae Hwa Young.

103
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:37,600
There has to be a place I haven't looked.

104
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,540
Mom?

105
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:55,790
Good thing I memorized the unlock pattern.

106
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,990
(Hwa Young, let's meet. We need to talk.)

107
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:01,130
What's this?

108
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:03,530
Why are there so many texts
from Professor Kang Nam Bong?

109
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:05,730
There are missed calls, too.

110
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:07,900
What's going on between them?

111
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,410
Seo Rin, what are you doing in here?

112
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,440
Why are you looking at your mom's phone?

113
00:07:17,510 --> 00:07:18,580
You scared me!

114
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:20,240
Mrs. Yang,

115
00:07:21,210 --> 00:07:22,450
let's get out of here.

116
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:27,820
Please, just pretend you didn't see that.

117
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:29,850
Okay? Promise? Please.

118
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,520
All right.

119
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:36,490
You must be shaken up from the accident.
Is there anything you're craving?

120
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:43,730
I'd like a cold sweet rice drink
if you have any.

121
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,140
Sweet rice drink?

122
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:51,840
Why the sudden craving?

123
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,710
She used to throw a fit,

124
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:55,250
saying the rice grains
looked like maggots.

125
00:07:55,610 --> 00:07:56,980
And now all of a sudden,
she wants a sweet rice drink?

126
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:02,150
Does memory loss change your tastes, too?

127
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,920
That's strange.

128
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,790
So my dear Seo Rin is
craving a sweet rice drink?

129
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:14,400
But I thought Seo Rin didn't like
the sweet rice drink.

130
00:08:14,670 --> 00:08:16,100
What are you talking about?

131
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,900
She must remember...

132
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,400
how I used to spoon-feed it to her
when she was young.

133
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:22,670
Seo Rin, do you remember that?

134
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:25,440
Yes, I think I kind of do.

135
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:29,850
Good. Your memories will come back
one by one, so don't worry.

136
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:33,550
Does that mean her memory is coming back?

137
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:37,790
Grandfather, I'd like to go
back to work tomorrow.

138
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:41,430
- Already?
- I'm just so bored staying at home.

139
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:42,690
All right, then.

140
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:46,660
The doctor said you were cleared for work,
so just take it easy.

141
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,470
Thank you, Grandfather.

142
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:59,010
I have no corporate experience,
so I don't know if I can pull this off.

143
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,980
But I have to face it sooner or later.

144
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:10,620
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

145
00:09:12,590 --> 00:09:13,660
What?

146
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:16,890
The director at Dream Hotel
looks just like Jang Mi?

147
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:18,160
Yes.

148
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,730
My brother said...

149
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,330
that this director was also
in a car accident...

150
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,340
on the very same day as Jang Mi.

151
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:29,810
- What?
- So many coincidences are fate or staged.

152
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:33,040
Besides, we went to the hospital
to check, remember?

153
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:35,950
And we heard there was another patient
besides Jang Mi.

154
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:38,450
- But...
- She was either transferred...

155
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:41,290
or discharged immediately.

156
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:43,890
Or someone pulled some strings.

157
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:47,090
There are plenty of ways to keep something
off the record.

158
00:09:48,130 --> 00:09:50,960
- So, what's your plan?
- I need to go see CEO Chae.

159
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:52,630
CEO Chae?

160
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:04,040
Just do as I said and wrap it up.

161
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:08,750
We keep getting complaints because
the room service is unacceptable.

162
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:10,750
Don't let it happen again.

163
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:12,350
Get on it.

164
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:29,030
I need to figure out how
Chae Hwa Young took my dad...

165
00:10:29,770 --> 00:10:31,400
to where the accident happened using
that security camera.

166
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:45,750
Baek Ho.

167
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,490
I've missed you.

168
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:55,530
- Let's go.
- Right.

169
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,460
What are Tae Pyung and Baek Ho...

170
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,630
doing here?

171
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:10,010
- What is it?
- Where are you?

172
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:12,210
They said you hadn't arrived
at the General Manager's office yet.

173
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,810
How am I supposed to know
where his office is?

174
00:11:15,210 --> 00:11:16,350
I'm in the lobby.

175
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:18,620
Fine, I'll send Manager Lee to get you.

176
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:21,150
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

177
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:29,660
I’ll be going now.

178
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:32,730
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

179
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:36,470
Goodness.

180
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:39,540
I can't believe I'm seeing
Chef Kang Jun Ho,

181
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:41,810
my old crush, this close.

182
00:11:42,810 --> 00:11:43,810
Are you all right?

183
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:47,550
I am now.

184
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,550
Please, have a seat for a moment.

185
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:04,460
Look at Ma Seo Rin, so prim and proper
in front of the guy she likes.

186
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,300
Is this a new act?

187
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,630
How ridiculous.

188
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,310
Doesn't that seem strange to you?

189
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:18,040
The nurse was positive...

190
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:21,010
that someone else had come
in the ambulance with Jang Mi.

191
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,150
But they vanished from the records.

192
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,380
That's impossible.

193
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:25,680
CEO Chae.

194
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,950
Is Director Ma doing okay?

195
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:29,350
Director Ma? Why do you ask?

196
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,160
From what I remember,

197
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:33,960
Director Ma and Jang Mi
look strikingly similar.

198
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,260
The fact that they were both
in an accident on the same day...

199
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:37,360
is bothering me.

200
00:12:37,530 --> 00:12:38,630
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

201
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,900
What are you trying to imply?

202
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:43,400
There's something I'd like to confirm
with Director Ma.

203
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:45,170
Could you please have her come here?

204
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,440
What could you possibly need to confirm
for you to barge in like this...

205
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,510
when I'm busy?

206
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:51,240
Baek Ho, if it's revealed that...

207
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,710
Seo Rin and I are twins
before I find any hard evidence,

208
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:56,680
there's no telling what Chae Hwa Young
will do to cover it up.

209
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,280
Seo Rin.

210
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:02,690
Seo Rin?

211
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,460
- Director Ma Seo Rin?
- Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

212
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,190
Don't you think
you're being incredibly rude?

213
00:13:22,770 --> 00:13:23,810
What are you doing?

214
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:28,050
Sorry. I was just going to show you
to the Dream Project office.

215
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:29,980
Is this the office?

216
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:32,550
I can go in by myself,
so you should go check on my mom.

217
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:34,690
It looked like she had guests anyway.

218
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:35,920
Right.

219
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:43,690
I guess I don't have to worry
about running into Baek Ho.

220
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:46,660
Chae Hwa Young and Manager Lee
will make sure to keep him away.

221
00:13:47,230 --> 00:13:49,130
They must have been afraid
I'd run into Seo Rin,

222
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:51,340
and that's why they never let me
set foot in the company.

223
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:52,770
Monsters.

224
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:58,740
Wait, where'd she go?

225
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:01,480
I'm very sorry about what happened
to Jang Mi.

226
00:14:02,150 --> 00:14:05,450
But that doesn't give you the right
to storm in and make demands.

227
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:06,780
That's rude.

228
00:14:06,780 --> 00:14:09,490
- It's just...
- We apologize.

229
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:12,460
We will find a way to meet
Ma Seo Rin on our own.

230
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,990
Listen here, Lawyer Kang!

231
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:16,690
Why on earth do you insist
on meeting my daughter?

232
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,260
Just drop it.

233
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,630
And stay away from the company
from now on.

234
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:24,670
We apologize for the intrusion.
Let's go, Tae Pyung.

235
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:36,710
Why do they keep popping up
like cockroaches?

236
00:14:43,490 --> 00:14:45,560
- What's going on?
- Where's Seo Rin?

237
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:47,320
I just escorted her to the office.

238
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:50,190
You have to stop Kang Baek Ho
from meeting Seo Rin.

239
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,200
At all costs.

240
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:54,060
Understood. It's time for your meeting.

241
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:55,930
We still have a little time, don't we?

242
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,900
I have to go see my son first.

243
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,770
When are you...

244
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:04,880
going to tell Jun Ho the truth?

245
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:06,910
Now's not the time.

246
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:11,720
How could I possibly face Jun Ho
and call myself his mother?

247
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:13,420
After Jun Ho...

248
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,850
marries Seo Rin,

249
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,690
and after I've given him everything
I possibly can,

250
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:19,790
I will tell him...

251
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:21,930
that I'm his mother.

252
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:30,570
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

253
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:33,240
General Manager Kang.
I see you haven't left yet.

254
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:35,670
Let's grab a coffee
and head over together.

255
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:37,610
Okay?

256
00:15:38,210 --> 00:15:40,810
Please look after Seo Rin for me.

257
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:42,580
Of course.

258
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:46,080
It seems the accident had a bigger toll
on her than I thought.

259
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,420
I hear she has amnesia.

260
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:51,920
Right. I'm sure she'll be fine soon.

261
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,930
All you have to do is follow my lead,
General Manager Kang.

262
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:02,470
I'll make it crystal clear to everyone
that you're on my side.

263
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:06,070
- I don't need to take sides.
- But I do.

264
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:10,070
- At least for Seo Rin's sake.
- Director Ma...

265
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:13,540
is a long way from delivering results
for this company.

266
00:16:14,350 --> 00:16:17,410
She did just get back to work,
so that's to be expected.

267
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:21,190
That's why I need you
to teach Seo Rin the ropes...

268
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:24,590
and make her a true asset to Dream Hotel.

269
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,690
I don't think that's the right approach.

270
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:29,130
- What?
- I hate to say this about her...

271
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,830
when she is unwell,

272
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:33,800
but can we expect her to perform well?

273
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,800
General Manager Kang.

274
00:16:35,470 --> 00:16:39,800
Eventually, you're the one
who will have to run Dream Hotel.

275
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:43,040
My Seo Rin is completely hopeless
when it comes to business.

276
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,410
Do you see what I'm getting at?

277
00:16:47,780 --> 00:16:48,980
Are you serious?

278
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:52,120
When I told you to be ambitious,
I meant it.

279
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:56,720
I see you as the perfect match
for my Seo Rin,

280
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:59,790
and I want you to run Dream Hotel.

281
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,430
I mean it.

282
00:17:06,830 --> 00:17:10,900
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

283
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:14,940
You should answer that.

284
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,210
Yes, hello?

285
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:22,510
Hwa Young.

286
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,450
I couldn't reach you,

287
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:25,950
so I wanted to make sure
you were all right.

288
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:28,520
How's Director Ma doing?

289
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,290
It must've been so hard on you.

290
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:34,390
Yes. Thank you for your concern.

291
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:37,730
Director Ma returned to the office today.

292
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:42,730
I have to go to a meeting now,
so I'll have to talk to you later.

293
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:46,640
Okay. I'll talk to you later then.

294
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:54,550
Unbelievable.

295
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:56,710
Hwa Young...

296
00:17:57,650 --> 00:18:01,150
is only being professional, right?
She was so cold.

297
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:03,090
Could she be upset with me
about something?

298
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:06,990
Should I go pay her a visit?

299
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:11,660
Right. If there's a misunderstanding,
we need to clear the air immediately.

300
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:20,370
Director Ma.

301
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:23,340
Excuse me.

302
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:26,410
I need to check something.

303
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:30,550
The executive parking lot is on B3, right?

304
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:32,280
Yes, ma'am.

305
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:36,190
Someone scratched my car and left.

306
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:37,990
This isn't the first time it's happened.

307
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:40,520
Okay. Do you happen to remember the date?

308
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:43,760
January 14, around 4:30 p.m.

309
00:18:57,370 --> 00:19:00,610
Our vegetables are delivered fresh daily,
so they're super fresh.

310
00:19:01,210 --> 00:19:03,180
Yes, they look really fresh.

311
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:05,350
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thanks.

312
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:17,090
Mom, would you like something else?

313
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:20,100
This is delicious. Bo Ra likes it a lot.

314
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:22,000
Mom, can I have more shrimp?

315
00:19:22,330 --> 00:19:25,900
Suk Hee is eating plenty of
shrimp and meat herself.

316
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:29,710
- Suk Hee is eating a lot.
- I'll get you more shrimp. Go on, eat up.

317
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:49,760
Director Ma.

318
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:51,760
It's just...

319
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,840
You mean there is no footage...

320
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:02,510
because the CCTV was broken
in the executive parking lot at that time?

321
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,210
Yes, I'm very sorry.

322
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:11,050
All right then,
I'll check who entered and left the hotel.

323
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:14,150
So please put the main entrance footage
on this for me.

324
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:16,790
And any other footage you can retrieve.

325
00:20:17,490 --> 00:20:18,590
Yes, ma'am.

326
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:19,890
And one more thing.

327
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:23,390
My mom and Manager Lee would worry
if they knew I was here,

328
00:20:23,460 --> 00:20:24,660
so please keep this quiet.

329
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:28,230
If word gets out about my car,
this whole hotel will be in an uproar.

330
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:30,830
You don't want that kind of trouble,
do you?

331
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,500
Yes, of course.

332
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:41,480
(Central Control Room)

333
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:47,280
On the day my dad died,

334
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:50,220
they said the parking lot
CCTVs were off for maintenance.

335
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:53,160
There's no way a hotel this big
has such lax security.

336
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:56,490
You worked hard to destroy the proof,
didn't you, Chae Hwa Young?

337
00:20:57,660 --> 00:20:59,000
But no matter how hard you try to hide it,

338
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,900
I'm sure there's something
you failed to cover up.

339
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:18,520
Lawyer Kang.

340
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,220
Jin Hong Ju.

341
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:23,090
So you remember my name now?

342
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,990
Doors closing.

343
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:26,560
Hold on.

344
00:21:27,090 --> 00:21:28,830
- Doors opening.
- Get in, Lawyer Kang.

345
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:30,590
Or I should say, Baek Ho.

346
00:21:37,230 --> 00:21:39,300
- Doors closing.
- Baek Ho,

347
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,340
did you by any chance come here to see me?

348
00:21:42,340 --> 00:21:43,370
No.

349
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,910
Actually, this worked out.

350
00:21:45,910 --> 00:21:47,610
I'm here to see Director Ma Seo Rin.

351
00:21:47,810 --> 00:21:49,580
Could you get her for me?

352
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,280
Director Ma? What for?

353
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:54,180
My sister Jang Mi looks like Director Ma,

354
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:55,550
and they both had an accident that day...

355
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:58,290
What are you talking about?
She looks nothing like her.

356
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:01,190
Welcome.

357
00:22:02,130 --> 00:22:06,300
No way.
Lawyer Kang is dating a woman like her?

358
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,600
The only thing they have in common,
from head to toe,

359
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:12,370
is that they happen to be the same gender.

360
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:13,640
Pardon?

361
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:16,740
But they definitely look alike.

362
00:22:16,870 --> 00:22:20,540
Actually, it's my lunch break,
so I was just on my way to your office.

363
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:21,710
So this is perfect.

364
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:34,390
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

365
00:22:35,130 --> 00:22:37,390
Oh my goodness, Professor.

366
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:40,000
Why would you just show up here
unannounced?

367
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:42,370
You've completely caught me off guard.

368
00:22:42,470 --> 00:22:45,670
I came because I was worried
you had the wrong idea about me.

369
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:47,440
The wrong idea? About what?

370
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:50,840
Then why have you been so cold to me
on the phone?

371
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:54,180
I miss you so much that
all I do is think about you all day.

372
00:22:55,310 --> 00:22:57,380
Don't you feel the same?

373
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,650
I've been thinking of you too, Professor.

374
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:02,290
I've missed you so much.

375
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:07,460
But I can't talk for long at work,
and sometimes it's just a bad time.

376
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,190
That's a relief.

377
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:14,400
As long as there's no misunderstanding,
that's all that matters.

378
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:17,270
My coworkers might see,
so you should go now.

379
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:21,170
Let's meet up somewhere else.
All right, Professor?

380
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:25,040
All right. Let's meet tomorrow, then.

381
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:26,680
Okay.

382
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,560
This man is Kang Baek Ho's father.

383
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,700
He's the one who ran over our dad
and killed him.

384
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:55,970
(Professor Kang Nam Bong,
Korea University)

385
00:23:56,970 --> 00:24:01,040
So Chae Hwa Young is seeing him
even though he's married?

386
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:37,250
This man is...

387
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:41,250
This is the guy.

388
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:44,190
(Public Release of Suspect Information,
Name: Park Soon Sun)

389
00:24:44,450 --> 00:24:45,560
That's Ssangkal.

390
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,490
He was there the day Dad died?

391
00:24:57,430 --> 00:24:58,940
Manager Lee and Ssangkal...

392
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,440
That's it.

393
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:02,940
My dad...

394
00:25:03,510 --> 00:25:06,140
could have died at the hands of those two.

395
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:08,710
And I bet Chae Hwa Young ordered it.

396
00:25:09,750 --> 00:25:10,750
But...

397
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:14,580
why did they put my dad in a car
and drive him so far away to kill him?

398
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:20,060
Chae Hwa Young.

399
00:25:20,860 --> 00:25:22,960
She's my sworn enemy
who had my dad killed.

400
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:37,940
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

401
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,650
(See you at the Dream Hotel coffee shop
at 2:00 p.m. From Your Love)

402
00:25:55,030 --> 00:25:57,190
Did Professor Kang stop by again already?

403
00:25:58,630 --> 00:26:00,330
What if someone saw him?

404
00:26:05,770 --> 00:26:08,100
- Hey, you!
- My goodness. What is this?

405
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:10,040
Darn you...

406
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:12,180
- What is this?
- It was you, wasn't it?

407
00:26:12,180 --> 00:26:15,350
In broad daylight,
you lured my husband to this dump?

408
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:16,380
That's not true.

409
00:26:16,450 --> 00:26:17,450
Get away from me!

410
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,020
No, you've got the wrong person!

411
00:26:19,020 --> 00:26:20,620
- Get away!
- Let go of me.

412
00:26:21,420 --> 00:26:23,020
What do you mean "wrong person?"

413
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:25,920
They say you've been a faithful widow
for 30 years?

414
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:29,260
So you must've been desperate
all those long, lonely nights, right?

415
00:26:29,390 --> 00:26:32,160
Is that why you lure any man you find
to this hotel?

416
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,230
What did you just say?

417
00:26:33,560 --> 00:26:35,770
Do you have any idea who I am?

418
00:26:35,770 --> 00:26:36,900
What did you say?

419
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:41,040
You have the nerve to run your mouth
after seducing my husband.

420
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:44,310
This is so absurd I'm speechless.
Listen here.

421
00:26:44,310 --> 00:26:45,810
Do you even know where you are?

422
00:26:45,940 --> 00:26:47,080
Why are you just standing there?

423
00:26:47,140 --> 00:26:48,680
Get this woman out of here, now!

424
00:26:48,810 --> 00:26:49,850
Why, you...

425
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:51,610
Darn it. Get off me!

426
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:54,320
You lunatic...

427
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:57,220
- You can't act like this here.
- A tramp like you...

428
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:59,320
Unbelievable.

429
00:27:01,620 --> 00:27:03,060
Here, take this!

430
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:05,030
Here, take this!

431
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:07,060
Take this!

432
00:27:08,530 --> 00:27:09,570
Goodness.

433
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:12,870
Let me go. Hey, you homewrecker!

434
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:32,990
(The First Man)

435
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:35,430
Mom, a video of you
is all over the Internet.

436
00:27:35,860 --> 00:27:37,290
The "Nation's Homewrecker?"

437
00:27:37,290 --> 00:27:39,330
Tell them to take it down. Now!

438
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:42,070
What if she realizes I'm not Seo Rin?

439
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:45,040
Jang Mi, you have to become Ma Seo Rin.

440
00:27:45,370 --> 00:27:48,170
Get me a list of everyone
who entered my office today.

441
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:49,640
Seo Rin?

442
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:52,110
What if it's not Seo Rin,
but her twin, Oh Jang Mi?

443
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:01,050
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
